<title>BRAZIL: Brazil telecoms to invest $11 bln a year - paper.</title>
<headline>Brazil telecoms to invest $11 bln a year - paper.</headline>
<dateline>RIO DE JANEIRO 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazilian telecommunications firms will be investing between $7 billion and $11 billion a year until 1999 on importing equipment to prepare for the privatization of the sector, an Industry and Commerce Ministry study said, according to a newspaper.</p>
<p>The study, cited by O Globo newspaper, shows Brazil to be the largest and fastest growing market for telecommunications products with a growth rate of 50 percent a year, O Globo said.</p>
